messages.content: Which brand has the most stock available?

```python
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Read the CSV file
url = "/api/files/mRiGSsHE49gH07OV.csv"
df = pd.read_csv(url)

# Group by brand and sum the stock
brand_stock = df.groupby('Brand')['Stock'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)

# Get the brand with the most stock
top_brand = brand_stock.index[0]
top_stock = brand_stock.iloc[0]

print(f"The brand with the most stock is '{top_brand}' with {top_stock} items in stock.")

# Create a bar chart showing top 10 brands by stock
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
brand_stock.head(10).plot(kind='bar')
plt.title('Top 10 Brands by Total Stock')
plt.xlabel('Brand')
plt.ylabel('Total Stock')
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
```

import pandas as pd

url = "/api/files/mRiGSsHE49gH07OV.csv"
df = pd.read_csv(url)

# Get the list of product names
product_names = df['Name'].tolist()

# Display the first 10 product names
print("产品名称列表（前10个）：")
for i, name in enumerate(product_names[:10], 1):
    print(f"{i}. {name}")

# Show total count
print(f"\n总共 {len(product_names)} 个产品。")
